    "faq_46wWyJ": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "accordion_MzkneT": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What color wavelengths does Q-Rejuvalight Pro have?",
            "text": "<p>The Q-Rejuvalight Pro has a total of 5 clinically studied wavelengths of light:<br/></p><ul><li>Infrared light (880 nm): Helps support circulation, protects existing collagen, and enhances product absorption.</li><li>Deep Red (660 nm): Supports skin recovery to help fade the look of marks and smooth texture.</li><li>Red (630 nm): Helps improve the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles while soothing visible redness.</li><li>Amber (605 nm): Helps visibly even skin tone and calm the look of redness.</li><li>Blue (415 nm): Helps reduce the look of breakouts and calm the appearance of irritation.</li></ul><p>There are two treatment modes:<br/></p><p>The Skin Rejuvenating Mode combines red, deep red, infrared, and amber wavelengths. This blend is designed to help visibly smooth, firm, and refresh the look of skin.</p><p>The Skin Clearing Mode combines red and blue wavelengths to help improve the appearance of mild-to-moderate inflammatory acne, supporting a clearer-looking complexion.<br/></p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_HnKbr6": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How quickly will I see results?",
            "text": "<p>Every individual may respond differently to specific wavelengths of light, and results will depend on the goal you want to address.<br/><br/>Most users report visible improvements in the look of breakouts and redness sooner than expected. Smoother-looking lines, improved tone, and a firmer appearance may take longer.<br/><br/>Changes are often gradual, so we recommend taking “before and after” photos to track your results. Consistency is key for maintaining improvements over time.</p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_wdHAce": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Is it safe for all skin types?",
            "text": "<p>Yes — the Q-Rejuvalight Pro is designed for use across all skin types when used as directed.<br/><br/>That said, skin types V and VI (on the Fitzpatrick scale) may be more sensitive to visible light due to higher melanin levels, leading to increased photo-absorption and a small risk of pigmentation changes.<br/><br/>Because of this, we advise that those with darker skin tones or pigment-prone skin consult with their dermatologist before use to determine proper settings and usage frequency.<br/><br/>Many users with deeper skin tones have used the device safely and shared positive outcomes when protocols were followed carefully.</p>",
            "link_url": "",
